topblock_final.title: WEC Ocala Spring 2026
topblock_final.copy:
From March 25 to April 5, 2026, the World Equestrian Center - Ocala hosts two weeks of exceptional hunter and jamper sport during the WEC Ocala Spring Series. Set in Florida’s Herse Capital of the World, this spring circuit brings together top riders for Hunter (Regional) and Jumper Level 2 competition across world-class arenas.
    
    Competitors and spectators alike enjoy the WEC’s remarkable amenities — climate-controlled indoor arenas, premium stabling, on-site lodging, and dining —  all within a premier equestrian resort environment. Mild spring temperatures and Ocala’s rich horse heritage make this an essential stop on the USEF Zone 4 calendar and a highlight of the 2026 show season.
